Hi Dave,

"Too Cold" means just that... I guess what I mean is that "too cold"  
= conditions that would render the event uncomfortable and  
impractical, despite all reasonable efforts.

Like a -40 wind chill, for instance... that would be too cold to be  
comfortable no matter how high you built the fire.  Even if you built  
up the fire real huge in those conditions you'd be baking your face  
and freezing your butt at the same time unless you stand there and  
pirouette like a chicken on a spit.  We try to avoid that kind of  
weather; it's "too cold". I asked quite a few of the newcomers if  
they thought that it was "too cold" to have a good time and none of  
them thought that was the case.


Happy Trails,

Greg Potts
