--- Greg Potts <greg(-at-)pottsfamily.ca> wrote:

The Canadian Bus Camping season is now officially
open!!

The turnout at TCWBC was outstanding: 15 buses
showed up this year,
including 2 eurovans, 5 vanagons and 8 Baywindow
buses.  That's more
than double the turnout from last year.  We burned
through a metric
busload of firewood, and had a great time.

The weather on Saturday was just about perfect for a
winter campout,
with more than a foot of fresh powdered snow on the
ground and not
too cold. The moon shone brightly through the woods
and the campfire
circle was well attended.
